entry.title: [Autofill] Preserve FormForest::FrameData if the frame survives
entry.content:
Consider a parent and a child frame with a frame transcending form.

Suppose a same-origin navigation in the child frame leads to another

document that contains another form.



This CL fixes that this new child form wasn't flattened immediately

into the parent form.



Before this CL, the navigation discarded the entire

FormForest::FrameData of the child frame. Thus, the FormForest

"forgot" the FormGlobalId of the child frame's parent form. Therefore,

when the FormForest saw the new child form, it triggered a reparse in

the parent frame. But that reparse was a no-op because the parent

frame's FormData hadn't changed at all (in particular, the child

frame's token hadn't changed).



This CL fixes this issue: FormForest now deletes the

FormForest::FrameData only if the ContentAutofillDriver is actually

going to be destroyed.

entry.title: Fix equal_range use in ServiceWorkerTaskQueue
entry.content:
If ServiceWorkerTaskQueue::StopObserving() is called with a

ServiceWorkerContext that does not exist in the

observing_worker_contexts_, there is a possibility of equal_range()

to return something different than observing_worker_contexts_.end()

and we end up removing an incorrect ServiceWorkerContext from the

multiset.



An indicator that the element we are searching was not found is that

the returned range iterators are equal. Return early if

StopObserving() was called with a ServiceWorkerContext not in the

multiset.

entry.title: Fix test flakiness in UndoCommitNavigation browser tests.
entry.content:
The subframe navigation test for UndoCommitNavigation was serving two

purposes:

- verifying that undo-commit-navigation or navigation-queueing worked

as expected, depending on the feature flag.

- that PerformanceManager did not crash with an inconsistent frame tree



It turns out that the race was subtly flaky because it installed the

interceptor for `DidCommitProvisionalLoad()` after an `ExecJs()` call.

`ExecJs()` runs the event loop to wait for the result of executing the

JS; however, this means that it might have already received and handled

`DidCommitProvisionalLoad()` before the interceptor was installed.



The fix is to install the interceptor before calling `ExecJs()` to

exercise the PerformanceManager-specific code paths.



In addition, this CL rearranges the browser tests by splitting tests

specific to `UndoCommitNavigation()` into their own test suite. This

saves test execution time since it takes a non-trivial amount of time

to set up the browser test, even for a skipped test–and more

importantly, it allows these tests to be tracked for removal in the

future when the legacy `UndoCommitNavigation()` path is removed.



Finally, the original subframe test for the `CommitNavigation()` race

has been restructured to more closely resemble how the main frame test

works: both tests now start at a.com, start a navigation to b.com, and

race that b.com navigation with a subsequent c.com navigation.



Bug: 1220337

entry.content:
Experimental type which enables select use cases to establish Mojo

interface receiver that receives its IPCs directly on its binding thread

without a hop through the process's IO thread first.

could be to have Mojo manage thread-local node overrides, pending a

bunch of other changes that would be needed first.



For now this is defined so that Chrome developers can experiment with

specific use cases, like the renderer's input handler on its compositor

thread.

entry.title: Refactor VideoCaptureDeviceClient::OnIncomingCapturedData()
entry.content:
Refactor & reorganize some code in OnIncomingCapturedData().

There should be no functional change, just adding consts and moving

things around so that they appear closer to where their values are

computable. Also switching some cheap DCHECKs into CHECKs.



Additionally, removed a test case that intentionally violated DCHECKs.

Since those are now CHECKs, the test case crashes instead of silently

failing. Moreover, the second test within that case was probably not

correct, since it introduced an unused `kFrameFormatNV12` constant.



This should help with future work in this method where some of the

computed variables will become useful in a different codepath.

Reason for revert: Test failure ReadAnythingAppTest.OnSelectionChange_NothingSelectedOnLoadingScreenSelection on several Linux builders (e.g. https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/Linux%20Tests/129835/overview, https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chrome/builders/ci/linux-chromeos-chrome/32505/overview) and Win10 Tests x64 (https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/Win10%20Tests%20x64/80117/overview)

> Reland "[Read Anything] Test the Read Anything WebUI in a browsertest."

>

> This is a reland of commit 8f3988a8e799e821754db7ad4fa1d4c6f103ae47

>

> The original change failed in an msan build because of uninitialized

> values in the text AXNodes. This reland fixes that by ensuring that

> we only set values in AXNodeData if the value was actually passed in

> from the js; i.e. if the conversion from v8 is successful. This

> modification is done in ReadAnythingAppController.

>

> Original change's description:

> > [Read Anything] Test the Read Anything WebUI in a browsertest.

> >

> > The webui test architecture was not designed to handle untrusted

> > tests. This CL replaces the webui test read_anything_app_test.ts with

> > a new browsertest, read_anything_app_browsertest.cc. It uses EvalJs

> > to inject the scripts written in read_anything_app_test.ts. The

> > trade-off is that this won’t check for untrusted sources being added.

> >

> > Alternatives explored:

> > 1. Migrate test to chrome-untrusted://. This would require upgrading

> > the infrastructure which was explored in

> > https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4292217/

> > but which would need further design to land.

> > 2. Test in chrome:// with iframe of the chrome-untrusted:// UI. This

> > requires handling communication across the iframe. Future debugging

> > might be tricky.

> > 3. Serve webui as trusted just in test build. This means a diverging

> > implementation and test.

entry.title: [omnibox][actions] Separates "takeover" actions from regular actions
entry.content:
Takeover actions are actions that take over the match navigation.

if one is provided, when the user selects the match, the navigation

is ignored and the takeover action is executed instead.



Currently takeover actions are supplied on the `ACMatch::actions_`

alongside the other actions. A bit in the `OmniboxAction` is used

to track whether an action is takeover or not. As opposed to regular

actions, takeover actions are not shown in the UI. Instead they are

used to intercept the match navigation in `OmniboxEditModel::OpenMatch`.



The fact that these types of actions are not shown in the UI makes the

UI and model to go out of sync and makes it difficult to verify whether

an action index refers to a valid action when match is being executed

by the realbox. See crrev.com/c/4419167 for reference. Besides that,

this special treatment creates complexities in the model and the UI.



To avoid these problems, this CL introduces a new `takeover_action`

field on the ACMatch. As opposed to the regular visible actions, the

default action is not shown in the UI and will execute instead of the

default match navigation in `OmniboxEditModel::OpenMatch`.

entry.title: Convert VrUiHostImpl to hold WebContents by WeakPtr
entry.content:
The VrUiHostImpl doesn't own the WebContents, and is not a

WebContentsObserver. This can lead to some racy destruction behavior.

The WebContentsObserver class discourages becoming one solely to check

for destruction and to instead leverage WeakPtrs instead, which is what

this converts the VrUiHostImpl to do.



I inspected the callers of VrUiHostImpl and determined that they

immediately acquire the WebContents before they use it, so it is okay

for their call patterns to remain as they are (including passing a raw

pointer into the VrUiHostImpl), and that only how VrUiHostImpl stashes

the WebContents that needs to be updated.



Fixed: 1432891

entry.title: Support non-preferred canvas formats
entry.content:
This CL supports required formats that aren't supported by the

underlying OS (`bgra8unorm` on Android, `rgba8unorm` on Mac) by

allocating a temporary texture of the desired format and copying

it to a supported texture format when it's time to present.



This should be seen at a fallback, last resort path, and if

more efficient ways of supporting the formats in question are

available they should be preferred.



Also adds a mechanism for reporting singleton warnings: Messages

that only show once per device to avoid spamming the user but

can provide performance/correctness nudges.

entry.title: HTTPS Upgrades: Fix crash with iframes containing bad HTTPS URLs
entry.content:
This CL fixes a crash that was introduced by the Site Engagement

heuristic changes. The SE heuristic is intended to enable HTTPS-First

Mode on sites with which the user interacts with regularly. If the

HTTPS URL of the site has a high enough Site Engagement score, HFM will

be enabled on the site eventually. For now, SE heuristic only records

metrics.



SE heuristic introduced a new field called interstitial_state_ which

gets created in the HTTPS Upgrade interceptor's MaybeCreateLoader() if

the load is eligible for HTTPS Upgrades (e.g. is a main frame load, has

GET method etc). interstitial_state_ is then checked in

MaybeCreateLoaderForResponse() to see if any metrics should be recorded

for the load. If the load isn't eligible for upgrades and

interstitial_state_ doesn't get instantiated in MaybeCreateLoader(),

MaybeCreateLoaderForResponse() crashes with a null deref.



This CL adds a browser test to simulate this scenario. It also adds a

main frame check in MaybeCreateLoaderForResponse() to avoid

dereferencing a null interstitial_state_.



Another alternative is to make interstitial_state_ a stack allocated

member to avoid the crash. However, this doesn't fix the underlying

issue of having interstitial_state_ not being populated properly for

ineligible navigations.

entry.title: hid: Unblock feature reports for mice and keyboards
entry.content:
Update IsAlwaysProtected to consider the type of report (input, output,

or feature) when deciding whether a report should always be blocked on

the basis of device capabilities.



chrome.hid and WebHID block access to mice and keyboards because

access to the input reports from these devices undermines the operating

system's security model by bypassing input focus restrictions.



Previously, feature reports were also blocked out of an abundance of

caution. However, blocking these reports also prevents applications from

accessing vendor-proprietary features that use feature reports.



This CL relaxes the blocking behavior so that feature reports can be

accessed even when the input and output reports are blocked.

entry.title: Android CCV/CRS: Turn on ChromeRootStoreUsed in fieldtial_testing_config.json
entry.content:
This required modifying tests to ensure that the test root is loaded in X509Utils.java via a ClassHook in ContentJUnit4ClassRunner before the user-added roots are pulled in net/cert/internal/trust_store_android.cc, so that the chrome cert verifier would correctly verify trust for connections to the EmbeddedTestServer. Previous attempts to do this did this at other points in the test loading process, but were unsuccessful for a variety of different reasons, usually in loading the root too late.



We also rely on the fact that the root cert for EmbeddedTestServer is a statically checked in file (at net/data/ssl/certificates/root_ca_cert.pem) as the current solution (starting up the EmbeddedTestServer in a separate APK + calling to get the root cert) requires calling into native code which can't be done easily before the chrome cert verifier loads the user-added roots.



This would be easier if the EmbeddedTestServer was run in process instead of in its own APK; I don't know if it would be feasible or how much work it would be to change this.
